Subject: Add timing support for constraint rules.

Full_Name: Chris Myers
Version: 
OS: 
source: 
log: 
Submission from: han.elen.utah.edu (155.99.23.196)
Submitted by: myers


Currently constraint rules only check untimed ordering relationships.
They should also check time separations.  In other words, when an enabled 
event fires it must meet its lower bound for all constraint rules.  Also,
the upper bound of no constraint rule can be allowed to exceed its upper
bound.

